This paper deals with comparisons between interpretations in description logics, which are a subfield of artificial intelligence and logic. The paper specifically focuses on conditions similar to bisimulations, which are commonly used in the study of logical systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). However, the paper also deals with concepts such as semi-positive concept assertions and the Hennessy-Milner property, which are relevant to areas such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the preservation and minimization of interpretations, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper specifically mentions description logics (cs.DL) as the field of study, making it a likely sub-category as well.
